<Algorithm code="           1. If _P_ is not a String, return *undefined*.           1. Let _index_ be CanonicalNumericIndexString(_P_).           1. If _index_ is not an integral Number, return *undefined*.           1. If _index_ is *-0*&lt;sub&gt;𝔽&lt;/sub&gt; or _index_ &lt; *-0*&lt;sub&gt;𝔽&lt;/sub&gt;, return *undefined*.           1. Let _str_ be _S_.[[StringData]].           1. Assert: _str_ is a String.           1. Let _len_ be the length of _str_.           1. If ℝ(_index_) ≥ _len_, return *undefined*.           1. Let _resultStr_ be the substring of _str_ from ℝ(_index_) to ℝ(_index_) + 1.           1. Return the PropertyDescriptor { [[Value]]: _resultStr_, [[Writable]]: *false*, [[Enumerable]]: *true*, [[Configurable]]: *false* }.         ">
